<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
You can get the quest by entering the quest entrance in Khazad-dum. There is currently no way to get the quest and its difficulty level on your list before you are in the middle of it. <p>
To take this quest you should be powerful enough to take on many non-unique greater demons of the worst sort, such as pit fiends and greater balrogs, since that is what you are going to face. Durin's Bane is a sissy compared to these guys. You are likely to end up having to kill many more than the initial number of demons for reasons of chain summoning. 
</p>
<p>
Mountain climbing ability is a great advantage in this quest since the walls are all hard rock. You can retreat to the walls to heal and you can stand in a wall to minimize the number of enemies you are fighting at once. 
</p>
<p>
The reward of extra house is of little value since the location is so inconvenient. However, because the demons drop good loot, the quest can be its own reward for a powerful character who gets lucky. 
</p>
